    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3140: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 23, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>155. Bolivian Minister today was informed by La Paz that State Department had
                    invited four neighbors to cooperate with Chaco neutrals in Washington. He was
                    urgently instructed to request acceptance by Peru and to request this Embassy to
                    support invitation to Foreign Office here.</p>
                <p>Embassy awaits instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
